cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning to achieve dynamic and efficient locomotion in a quadruped robot. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of AI techniques such as deep learning, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the study of the effects of spinal joint compliance and actuation on the robot's performance, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves simulation results, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category as well.
